benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/block - Block an account

covered: Valid Payload: Minimal and full payload scenarios tested (TC01, TC02).
Error Handling: Covered 400/404/401 responses (missing header, missing body, invalid accountId, account not found, unauthorized).
Query Parameters: Coverage across requestedDate and pluginProperty with TC02, TC03, TC04, TC15, TC18.
Security: SQL injection in accountId and malicious payload tested (TC13, TC14).
Edge Cases: Boundary conditions like max length (TC16), min values (TC17), empty pluginProperty (TC15), large payload (TC20).
Integration: Plugin interaction and plugin availability covered (TC21, TC22).
Regression: Duplicate BlockingState (TC23) and backward compatibility (TC24).
Performance: High concurrency and sustained load tests (TC25, TC26).
Accessibility: Documentation and error messages accessibility (TC27).
Error cases for non-existent account (TC06) and missing required header (TC08).
gaps: Authorization: No test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient privileges.
Server error handling: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error scenario (503 used for downtime).
Caching behavior: No tests for ETag/Cache-Control headers.
Rate limiting: No explicit 429 tests under burst load, despite high concurrency.
Data type validations within BlockingState payload: no tests focusing on invalid data types for fields in BlockingState.
recommendations: Add a 403 Forbidden test to cover insufficient privileges scenarios.
Add an explicit 500 Internal Server Error test path to validate server error semantics.
Add caching tests (ETag, Cache-Control) to verify caching behavior.
Add rate-limiting tests (429) under burst or high-load conditions.
Add targeted tests validating data types and field-level constraints within BlockingState payloads.
